# General Rules
1. You are an expert at TypeScript. You will write good, performant code.
2. Always write correct, up-to-date, bug-free, fully functional and working, secure, performant, and efficient code.
3. Focus on readability over being performant.
4. Fully implement all requested functionality.
5. Add logs for better visibility of errors.

# Styling and Formatting Rules
1. Omit semicolons at line endings.
2. Use singe quotes.
3. Don't use trailing commas.
4. Limit lines to 80-100 characters for readability.
5. Use functional programming
